    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-04T07:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-04T07:44:00-05:00" n="351"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.001/55: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reber</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-04T12:00:00-00:44"
                            >December 4, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>171. Department’s telegram No. 109, December 3, 5 p.m. The Constitution, article
                    3, section 2, states that the Legislature may provide for cases of resignation
                    of both President and Vice President declaring what officer shall act as
                    President. Section 971, Revised Statutes, further provides that in such an event
                    the Secretary of State shall discharge the duties of President until the
                    disability be removed or an election held.</p>
                <p>The President’s resignation was accepted by both Houses yesterday and Barclay
                    declared his lawful successor. No announcements of the latter’s program or new
                    cabinet have yet been made.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reber</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
